Insight-OSINT

1. Pre-Requisites
Ensure the target PC has the necessary software installed:
•	Python (Version 3.8 or later): 
https://www.python.org/downloads
•	Node.js and npm (Latest LTS version): https://nodejs.org/en/download

2. Extract the ZIP File
1.	Copy the ZIP file to the target PC.
2.	Extract the ZIP file into a desired folder, e.g., D:\IntelScope

3. Backend Setup
Step 1: Navigate to the Backend Folder
Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the backend directory:
cd <extracted-folder>/backend
Step 2: Create a Virtual Environment
Set up a virtual environment to manage dependencies:
python -m venv env
Step 3: Activate the Virtual Environment
•	Windows: env\Scripts\activate
•	macOS/Linux: source env/bin/activate
Step 4: Install Dependencies
Install the required Python libraries using: pip install -r requirements.txt
Step 5: Update API Keys
1. OpenAI API Key (ChatGPT Integration)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: OpenAI API Keys
•	Instructions:
o	Sign up or log in to your OpenAI account.
o	Navigate to the "API Keys" section.
o	Generate a new secret key and copy it.
________________________________________
2. Google Maps API Key (Geospatial Data)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: Google Cloud Console
•	Instructions:
o	Log in with a Google account.
o	Create a new project or use an existing one.
o	Enable the "Maps JavaScript API" and "Places API".
o	Generate an API key under the "Credentials" section.
________________________________________
3. NewsAPI (News Articles)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: NewsAPI
•	Instructions:
o	Sign up for a free or paid account.
o	Copy the API key provided in your account dashboard.
________________________________________
4. Reddit API (Discussions Data)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: Reddit App Preferences
•	Instructions:
o	Log in to Reddit and navigate to "Create App".
o	Choose "script" as the app type.
o	Note the "client ID" and "client secret".
________________________________________
5. PyTrends API (Google Trends Data)
•	Link: No API key is required for PyTrends.
o	It uses a Python package to interact with Google Trends. Ensure the package is properly installed via pip install pytrends.
________________________________________
6. Gemini API (Market Data)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: Gemini API
•	Instructions:
o	Log in to Gemini or create an account.
o	Navigate to "API Settings" under your account.
o	Generate a new API key and secret.
________________________________________
7. Semantic Scholar API (Research Papers)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: Semantic Scholar API
•	Instructions:
o	Sign up for a free account.
o	Access the API settings to generate a new API key.
________________________________________
8. CORE API (Open Access Research Papers)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: CORE API
•	Instructions:
o	Register on the CORE platform.
o	Navigate to the API section to generate a new API key.
________________________________________
9. IEEE Xplore API (Conference Papers)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: IEEE Xplore API
•	Instructions:
o	Sign up or log in to IEEE.
o	Request access to the Xplore API and generate an API key.
________________________________________
10. Twitter API (Social Media Data)
•	Link to Obtain API Key: Twitter Developer Portal
•	Instructions:
o	Sign up for a Twitter Developer account.
o	Create a new app in the developer portal.
o	Generate API keys, access tokens, and secrets.

4. Frontend Setup
Step 1: Navigate to the Frontend Folder
In the terminal, navigate to the frontend directory
cd <extracted-folder>/frontend
Step 2: Install Dependencies
Install all required npm packages:
npm install
Step 3: Start the Frontend
Run the React app:
npm start
•	The React app will start on http://localhost:3000.
________________________________________

Step 4. Testing the Project
1.	Open http://localhost:3000 in a browser.
2.	Perform a search query to test the backend and frontend integration.
3.	Validate the responses and ensure all features (e.g., Wikipedia fetch, Reddit discussions, ChatGPT responses) are working correctly.






















AFTER ALL SETUP:
OPEN 2 COMMAND PROMPTS:
IN 1ST COMMAND PROMPT: 
	d:
cd “Your path of backend file”                  e.g.: cd D:\IntelScope\backend
env\Scripts\activate
python app.py

IN 2ND COMMAND PROMPT:
D:
cd “Your path of frontend file”                  e.g.: cd D:\IntelScope\frontend
npm start
then The React app will start on http://localhost:3000




